  "text": "Procedures for DNA extraction from tissue have been described previously [CITATION_1] . In brief, 15 paraffin sections, each 5-mm thick, of gastric tissue samples were used for DNA extraction. Gastric tissues were retrieved using xylene and alcohol. The areas rich in gastric tumor cells were selected and carefully microdissected from the slides. Genomic DNA from microdissected tissue was isolated using the High Pure PCR Template Preparation kit (Boehringer Mannheim, Indianapolis, IN).",
